      <bioghist id="aspace_503f3badb254bf7c5539c5bfe5df27fe">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Edwin Cooley Mason (1831-1898) of Springfield, Ohio, was the son of United States Congressman Samson Mason (1793-1869) and Minerva Needham Mason (1805-1890). His birth followed those of his brother Rodney Mason (1824-1893) and sister Emily Mason Haynes (1827-1848).</p>
         <p>Edwin Cooley Mason served in the United States Army during the American Civil War and was brevetted Brigadier General, United States Volunteers on June 3, 1865. He later served in the United States Army in the Department of Columbia, 21st Infantry Regiment during the Modoc War (1872-1873), Nez Perce War (1877), and Bannock War (1878). He retired from the army in 1895. He was married to Frances Mary Kingsbury Mason (1844-1913), and they had four children: Kathro Montague Mason (1868-1930), Mary Needham Mason Moore (1870-1955), Frances Kingsbury Mason (1874-1907), and Charles Haynes Mason (1881-1951).</p>
         <p>Rodney Mason served as a colonel in the United States Army during the American Civil War and resigned in August 1862. He became a patent attorney in Washington, D.C., and was married to Mary Alice Camp Mason (1844-1924).</p>
      </bioghist>
